<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="70" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,1706,2019]" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,464,1886,1911]" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[769,856,1886,1910]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Macroderes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bias">
<emphasis box="[769,856,1886,1910]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">M. bias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
females through the combination of the following characters: punctate lateral borders of pronotum, elytra stria 9 contiguous to elytra stria 10, even punctuation of pronotum, anterolateral depressions of pronotum and the dense punctate and shagreened elytra, however, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1880" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Macroderes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pristinus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">M. pristinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[553,637,1995,2019]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Macroderes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bias">
<emphasis box="[553,637,1995,2019]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="70">M. bias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a more punctuated, flatter elytra striae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
